---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Contact — Action Models for Robot Learning"
  description="How to reach Pavan Kumar Kandapagari about the open-access textbook Action Models for Robot Learning."
  currentPath="contact"
>
  <main class="toc-page">
    <h1>Get in touch</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      Notes from readers are the most useful input this book has.
    </p>

    <p>
      Typo corrections, places where the argument is unclear, sections that don't deliver what
      their title promises, references I should have cited — all of it lands well. I read
      everything; replies are best-effort and may take a few days. Pick whichever channel below
      matches what you want to say.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>GitHub</strong> —
      <a href="https://github.com/kandapagari/in-action-book">github.com/kandapagari/in-action-book</a>.
      The natural home for typo corrections, draft feedback, open issues, and pull
      requests on the manuscript. Anything that benefits from being discussed in
      public belongs here.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Email</strong> —
      <a href="mailto:pavan.kandapagari@gmail.com">pavan.kandapagari@gmail.com</a>.
      Better for collaboration, longer-form questions, and anything that isn't
      suited to a public issue.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>LinkedIn</strong> —
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kandapagari/">linkedin.com/in/kandapagari</a>.
      Reasonable for professional introductions, talks, and conference invitations.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Personal site</strong> —
      <a href="https://kandapagari.vercel.app">kandapagari.vercel.app</a>.
      Broader notes and projects that sit outside this book.
    </p>

    <p>
      The book is open-access and the manuscript lives in public on GitHub;
      contributions of any size are welcome, including a single typo, a clearer figure caption, or a
      substantive rewrite of a section. See
      <a href="/about/">the about page</a> for what the book is and how it is
      being written.
    </p>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
